# UI Design System

## Primitives ŌĆö always check first

Before building any UI element, verify it already exists in `frontend/components/ui/`.

Available exports from `@/components/ui`:

| Export | File | Use for |
|---|---|---|
| `Button` | `Button.tsx` | All buttons; supports `variant` + `size` |
| `Input`, `Textarea` | `Input.tsx` | Text inputs; supports `inputSize` |
| `Modal` | `Modal.tsx` | Dialogs; controlled via `open`/`onClose` |
| `ConfirmDeleteModal` | `ConfirmDeleteModal.tsx` | Destructive-action confirmation |
| `Card` | `Card.tsx` | Content sections |
| `StatusBadge`, `SourceBadge`, `MatchBadge`, `CountBadge` | `Badge.tsx` | Status chips |
| `Pill` | `Pill.tsx` | Compact label tags |
| `FilterTabs` | `FilterTabs.tsx` | Horizontal filter bar |
| `PageHeader` | `PageHeader.tsx` | Page-level h1 + actions |
| `SectionLabel` | `SectionLabel.tsx` | Section headings within a page |
| `ThreeDotsMenu` | `ThreeDotsMenu.tsx` | Overflow action menus |
| `Amount` | `Amount.tsx` | Formatted currency amounts |
| `NavLink` | `NavLink.tsx` | Sidebar navigation links |
| `PrevNextNav` | `PrevNextNav.tsx` | Prev/next pagination on detail pages |
| `DateInput` | `DateInput.tsx` | Date picker input |

**Do not create a new primitive** unless none of the above serves the need.

## Styling Rules

- **Tailwind CSS only** for all styling. No inline `style={{}}` except where Tailwind cannot express the value.
- Use `clsx` for conditional class composition:

```tsx
import clsx from "clsx";
<div className={clsx("base-classes", condition && "conditional-class")} />
```

- Never use `tailwind-merge` directly ŌĆö `clsx` is the established convention here.

## Design Tokens (defined in `tailwind.config.ts`)

- **Accent color:** `bg-accent` / `text-accent` / `border-accent` ŌåÆ `#635bff`; hover: `bg-accent-hover` ŌåÆ `#5248db`. **Never hardcode `#635bff`.**
- **Sidebar background:** `bg-sidebar` ŌåÆ `#f6f9fc`
- **Status colors:** `bg-status-{pending,processing,done,failed,to_confirm}` and `text-status-{ŌĆ”}`
- **Font:** Inter is configured as `fontFamily.sans`; no other font should be imported.

## Component Variant Pattern

New components that need variants should follow the `Record<Variant, string>` pattern used in `Button.tsx` and `Input.tsx`:

```tsx
const variantClasses: Record<"primary" | "secondary", string> = {
  primary: "bg-accent text-white",
  secondary: "bg-white border border-gray-200 text-gray-700",
};
```

## Icons

- Use `lucide-react` exclusively. Do not install other icon libraries.
- Import individual icons: `import { ChevronRight, Plus } from "lucide-react"`.

## Feature Components

- Feature-level components live in `frontend/components/` (not `components/ui/`).
- They may use React Query, local state, and domain logic.
- Use `"use client"` when the component uses hooks or browser APIs.

